cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper presents a new network for solving continuous POMDPs by learning belief representations and leveraging them for planning. This involves introducing a novel particle filter network and a new planning algorithm over the belief representations. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves learning belief representations and uncertainty-dependent policies. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it presents a new network for solving POMDPs. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) as it involves continuous control and planning tasks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves state estimation and planning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as one of the tasks involves 3D navigation.
